yoruba_text: Nígbà tí ohun tí ẹ̀ ń bẹ̀rù bá dé bí ìjì, Tí àjálù yín sì dé bí ìjì líle, Nígbà tí ìdààmú àti wàhálà bá dé bá yín.
english_text: When what you dread comes like a storm, And your disaster arrives like a storm wind, When distress and trouble come upon you.

yoruba_text: Lójú-lójú là ń wo ẹni tí a óò kéwì fún.
english_text: It is directly in the eyes that one looks at the subject of the praise poem one is performing.

yoruba_text: Wà á kórira rẹ̀.
english_text: You will hate it.

yoruba_text: Ajá tó lè sáré là ń dẹ sí egbin.
english_text: It is a swift dog that one sends after a Kobe antelope.

yoruba_text: Yaroslav Sivulskiy, tó jẹ́ aṣojú Àjọ European Association of Jehovahs Witnesses, sọ pé: Bó tiẹ̀ jẹ́ pé a ò gbà pé a jẹ̀bi ẹ̀sùn náà, àmọ́ inú wa dùn pé Valeriy máa lè pa dà sílé.
english_text: Yaroslav Sivulskiy, a representative from the European Association of Jehovahs Witnesses, states: While we do not agree with the guilty verdict, we are glad that Valeriy can return home.

yoruba_text: Ó wá lọ odò ẹ̀sìnmìnrìn.
english_text: He came to the river Essinminrin.

yoruba_text: Bí Ọlọ́run ṣe parí dídá ọ̀run àti ayé àti gbogbo ohun tó wà nínú wọn nìyẹn.
english_text: Thus the heavens and the earth and everything in them were completed.

yoruba_text: Àwọn tó jẹ́ séríkí nínú àwọn ọmọ Ísọ̀ nìyí: Àwọn ọmọkùnrin Élífásì, àkọ́bí Ísọ̀ ni: Séríkí Témánì, Séríkí Ómárì, Séríkí Séfò, Séríkí Kénásì.
english_text: These are the sheikhs of the sons of Eʹsau: The sons of Elʹi·phaz, Eʹsaus firstborn: Sheikh Teʹman, Sheikh Oʹmar, Sheikh Zeʹpho, Sheikh Keʹnaz.

yoruba_text: Ìjọba Mexico ò kóyán àwọn àṣà Huichol kéré rárá, torí náà, dé ìwọ̀n àyè kan, ìjọba fún wọn lómìnira láti ṣe bó ṣe wù wọ́n.
english_text: Mexican national authorities respect Huichol traditions and culture to the extent of granting this society a certain degree of autonomy.

yoruba_text: ìdá mẹ́ta míì á wà ní Ẹnubodè Ìpìlẹ̀, ìdá mẹ́ta míì á sì wà ní ẹnubodè tó wà lẹ́yìn àwọn ẹ̀ṣọ́ ààfin.
english_text: another third will be at the Gate of the Foundation, and another third will be at the gate behind the palace guards.

yoruba_text: Ó mà sàn kéèyàn ní ọgbọ́n ju kó ní wúrà o! Ó sì dára kéèyàn ní òye ju kó ní fàdákà.
english_text: How much better to acquire wisdom than gold! To gain understanding is to be chosen over silver.

yoruba_text: Aboyún bí, ìhá tù ú.
english_text: The pregnant woman delivered; her sides are much eased.

yoruba_text: O ò gbọ́dọ̀ jalè.
english_text: Neither must you steal.

yoruba_text: Màá yin Jèhófà, ẹni tó fún mi ní ìmọ̀ràn.
english_text: I will praise Jehovah, who has given me advice.

yoruba_text: O máa sọ pé: Èmi yóò gbógun ja ilẹ̀ tí àwọn agbègbè rẹ̀ ṣí sílẹ̀.
english_text: You will say: I will invade the land of unprotected settlements.

yoruba_text: Díẹ̀-díẹ̀ lẹyẹ ń mu ọsàn.
english_text: It is bit by bit that a bird eats an orange.

yoruba_text: Bó ṣe wọ ilé Ọlọ́run, tí wọ́n sì jẹ àwọn búrẹ́dì tí wọ́n ń gbé síwájú, èyí tí kò bófin mu fún òun àti àwọn tó wà pẹ̀lú rẹ̀ láti jẹ, àfi àwọn àlùfáà nìkan.
english_text: How he entered into the house of God and they ate the loaves of presentation, something that it was not lawful for him or those with him to eat, but for the priests only.

yoruba_text: Ọmọ obìnrin yìí kú ní òru, torí pé ó sùn lé e.
english_text: During the night this womans son died, because she lay on him.

yoruba_text: Jèhófà, ìjẹ́mímọ́ ni ọ̀ṣọ́ ilé rẹ títí láé.
english_text: Holiness adorns your house, O Jehovah, for all times.

yoruba_text: Àmọ́ wọ́n rọ̀ ọ́ pé kó dúró, wọ́n ní: Dúró sọ́dọ̀ wa, torí ó ti ń di ọwọ́ alẹ́, ọjọ́ sì ti lọ, Ló bá wọlé, ó sì dúró sọ́dọ̀ wọn.
english_text: But they urged him to remain, saying: Stay with us, because it is almost evening and the day is nearly over, With that he went in to stay with them.

yoruba_text: Nígbà náà, Ábúsálómù àti gbogbo ọkùnrin Ísírẹ́lì sọ pé: Ìmọ̀ràn Húṣáì ará Áríkì dára ju ìmọ̀ràn Áhítófẹ́lì! Nítorí Jèhófà ti pinnu láti sọ ìmọ̀ràn rere Áhítófẹ́lì di asán, kí Jèhófà lè mú àjálù bá Ábúsálómù.
english_text: Then Abʹsa·lom and all the men of Israel said: The advice of Huʹshai the Arʹchite is better than the advice of A·hithʹo·phel! For Jehovah had determined to frustrate the sound advice of A·hithʹo·phel, so that Jehovah could bring disaster on Abʹsa·lom.

yoruba_text: Àyè kì í há adìẹ kó má dèé ìdí àbaa rẹ̀.
english_text: The space is never so tight that a chicken will not be able to reach its incubating nest.

yoruba_text: Lẹ́yìn náà, ó pa gbogbo àkọ́bí tó wà ní ilẹ̀ wọn, Ìbẹ̀rẹ̀ agbára ìbímọ wọn.
english_text: Then he struck down every firstborn in their land, The beginning of their procreative power.

yoruba_text: Akánjú jayé, ọ̀run wọn ò pẹ́.
english_text: People who live impatiently: their going to heaven is not far off.

yoruba_text: Ó tún wá gbósùbà fún ikọ̀ náà fún gudugudu méje, yàyà mẹfà tí wọn se láti gbógun ti ikọ̀ Boko Haram àti àwọn ọlọ̀tẹ̀ alákatakítí ẹlẹ́sìn mùsùlùmí, Islamic State of West Africa Province ISWAP ní ẹkùn náà.
english_text: He commended the troops for their gallantry in dealing with the boko haram and Islamic State of West Africa Province ISWAP terrorists in the region.

yoruba_text: Gbogbo ọjọ́ tí àrùn náà bá fi wà lára rẹ̀ ni yóò fi jẹ́ aláìmọ́.
english_text: He will be unclean the whole time that he has the disease.
